pageContext.claim: “Governor should call in the National Guard in Wisconsin. It is ready, willing, and more than able. End problem FAST!”
pageContext.analysis: The day before this tweet, Gov. Tony Evers of Wisconsin already had authorized the state National Guard to support local law enforcement in order to stem the violence that erupted after a white police officer on Aug. 23 shot and partially paralyzed Jacob Blake in front of his children.
